1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. f4 Bg7 5. Nf3 ({Moving on to the main line with} 5. Nf3 {.}) 5... c5 6. Bb5+ Bd7 7. Bxd7+ ({Besides the main} 7. e5 {, which is covered separately in great detail, this is the second most popular move. As we have seen so often before, this exchange only helps Black to develop the queenside pieces, and this can't really be good news for White.}) 7... Nbxd7 {The most natural recapture and also the strongest one. Both other reasonable captures are playable for Black and, in fact, have been played many times. But if we can develop the knight, why shouldn't we?} 8. e5 {This move looks tempting but doesn't quite work. To demonstrate this, Black needs to know a very important trick.} Nh5 {A very important trick. The availability of this square is vital for us. I must confess that in my 40 years in chess, I had never seen this position before preparing for this course. The knight looks trapped on h5 , but the attempts to catch it will come at a great cost.} 9. g4 {Since White's center is collapsing anyway, we might as well see what happens if White goes ahead and tries to catch the knight.} Nxf4 {Admit it, it's not a trick you see every day, right? The black knight sacrifices his life, but we get three central pawns in return. In fact, these are the very three pawns that constitute the Austrian Attack. Black's mass in the center will be a formidable force.} 10. Bxf4 cxd4 {This is the point, of course. After eliminating the f4 -pawn, we take another one in the very heart of White's position. Suddenly, it transpires that White can't recapture this annoying pawn. :)} 11. Ne4 {Unable to take the d4 -pawn, White needs to bring this knight into safety, and e4 seems like the best square.} dxe5 {The culmination of the plan that started a few moves ago. Black sacrificed the knight and got a dangerous central mass of pawns in return. I'm not saying it will be an easy cruise to victory from now on, but it's not a position that White would aim for from the opening. Black has many ways to fight for the initiative, and White will have to defend quite carefully.} *

