1. e4 d6 {Here, we'll take a very brief look at all sorts of early sidelines. The brevity of our attention is explained by the fact that, technically, all these lines are not part of the Pirc, so it's more of an overview than anything else.} 2. d4 {It's the main move, of course. The alternatives are plentiful but of sometimes dubious quality.} Nf6 ({This move, followed by 3...g6 , is an integral part of the Pirc. Technically, our opening only arrives after Nc3} 2... g6 {and we could skip all the other third moves altogether. Think of them as a bonus. :)}) 3. e5 {This move is a strangely frequent online reaction that should perhaps have been left unmentioned. :) Any other plausible move is better, and some are covered separately.} dxe5 4. dxe5 Qxd1+ 5. Kxd1 Ng4 {Black wins a central pawn, at the very least.} *

