1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. Be3 Bg7 {Here we will examine various sidelines that White is likely to use at a club level, especially online. As you will see very soon, they are not very dangerous.} 5. Qd2 c6 6. Bh6 {This move is quite direct and equally dangerous. It's not an invitation to panic but rather an appeal to pay close attention over the next few moves. :)} Bxh6 {This move is necessary. I don't want to castle and get mated after White plays h4 .} 7. Qxh6 e5 ({This is not the most popular move, as many prefer the elegant sortie with} 7... Qa5 {. Central strategies are usually stronger, though, and this position is no exception. Black establishes a strong presence in the middle of the board, and all we need to do is learn a few key lines.}) 8. O-O-O {This natural and popular move certainly deserves our attention. White maintains the pawn center and keeps the option of playing for the f4 break. There are also immediate threats along the d-file, so Black will need to proceed carefully over the next few moves.} Qe7 {Removing the queen from a dangerous file is a good, cautious move. The black queen has to stay close to keep the f6 -knight defended, as failing to do so could result in a devastating fork with Qg7 .} 9. h3 {This move is similar to the main line, as it also controls the g4 -square. Black's reaction remains the same.} Nbd7 {Once again, Black consolidates and develops before changing the pawn structure with ... b5 . Should White hesitate here, Black might also consider the plan of ... exd4 , followed by ... Nc5 .} 10. Nf3 {One of the key benefits of playing the line with h3 is being able to play this move without worrying about the consequences of ... Bg4 or ... Ng4 . The knight is quite happy here, plain and simple. :)} b5 {The time has come for our usual queenside expansion. Black hints at the possibility of ... b4 , but, more importantly, prepares to finish development by playing ... Bb7 and castling long. White cannot prevent this, and Black maintains a fair share of chances in this position.} *

