1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. f4 Bg7 {Here, we will consider White's various options on move 5, other than the main line with Nf3 .} 5. Bd3 {Of all the sidelines, this one is probably the best. The bishop is really well placed on d3 and defending e4 -pawn prevents ... c5 in a natural way. Nonetheless, Black has quite a number of satisfactory replies.} e5 {A very central way to play and also quite logical in a way because White was not doing anything to control the dark squares in the center. This movie is also made possible by the fact that the d3 -bishop blocks the d-file.} 6. Nf3 {Developing the knight looks natural enough, but this really doesn't cause any problems.} exd4 {It looks unusual to immediately abandon the fight for the center, but Black has a very concrete point.} 7. Nxd4 c6 {And this is the point! White doesn't have a good way to castle now and has to lose more time to finish their development. Black will have a very comfortable game.} *

