1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. f4 Bg7 5. Nf3 ({Moving on to the main line with} 5. Nf3 {.}) 5... c5 6. d5 {This is a very popular continuation, especially in those cases when White is not ready to challenge us in very topical theoretical variations. White hopes to keep their central pawns and castle, retaining some advantage. Black does get a few moves, however, to complicate matters.} O-O {As always, we castle first and think later. It is much easier to define the plans in the center of the board once the king has been tucked away safely.} 7. Be2 {This is a very possible way to develop the white pieces but doesn't pose any problems for Black. One of the drawbacks of having the bishop on e2 as opposed to d3 is that, in many lines, the e4 -pawn is not sufficiently protected. We have a wide choice of possible continuations here, and I'll show you what I think is the simplest.} e6 {Since White's last move did very little to control the center and to defend the e4 -pawn, it is very logical for Black to open up the e-file and get immediate counterplay. We could, of course, also go ... b5 and make it work, but the central strategy seems very easy for Black here.} 8. dxe6 {This capture looks logical, and White could be forgiven for thinking that the d6 -pawn could be weak later on. The truth is Black is very well developed and will easily achieve the central break with the timely ... d5 .} (8. O-O exd5 9. e5 Nfd7 {isn't dangerous for Black either.}) 8... Bxe6 ({Development first, of course. Recapturing} 8... fxe6 {would allow} 9. e5 {and lead to completely unnecessary suffering.}) 9. O-O {This move is possible of course, but it doesn't cause many problems for Black.} Nc6 {Black is the first one to finish development and now can choose from many promising plans. The natural and the standard plan with ... d6 - d5 will likely lead to equal play, but Black can be even more ambitious by playing ... Qb6 and ... Nd4 . The one thing we have to watch out for is that White doesn't get to play f4 - f5 under favorable circumstances.} *

